feat: Implement users layout using Jetpack Compose
This commit introduces the users layout, leveraging Jetpack Compose for a modern and dynamic user interface. The layout consists of a scrollable list of user items, each displaying the user's avatar, name, and additional details.
Key Features: - Users are displayed in a scrollable list, allowing for easy navigation. - Each user item includes an avatar, providing visual identification. - User names and additional details are prominently displayed for quick reference. - The layout is designed to be responsive and adapt to various screen sizes. - Dark theme compatibility ensures a consistent user experience across different themes.
Enhancements: - Improved layout structure for efficient rendering and performance optimization. - Utilized Compose's built-in components for seamless integration and consistency. - Incorporated state management techniques to handle user interactions and data updates. - Applied modern design principles for an aesthetically pleasing and intuitive user interface.
Future Improvements: - Implement pagination for large datasets to improve performance and loading times. - Enhance user item interactions with animations and gestures for a more engaging experience. - Integrate user search functionality to allow users to quickly find specific users. - Optimize layout for accessibility to ensure inclusivity and usability for all users.
Overall, this commit lays the foundation for a robust and user-friendly users layout, setting the stage for further enhancements and feature development in future iterations.

Enhancement: Added Jetpack Compose UI for OrdersActivity
Details: - Implemented OrdersActivity using Jetpack Compose to replace the existing XML layout. - Created reusable components for OrderCard and OrdersGrid. - Used LazyColumn for efficient rendering of order items.
Additional information: The Jetpack Compose implementation offers improved readability, maintainability, and performance compared to the XML layout. It also aligns with modern Android development practices.

Refine audit log and payment statistics queries in ApiController
Updated the ApiController to enhance the audit() function to filter logs based on the user's name and limit the data to the most recent 15 records. Simplified the paymentStatistics() function to calculate paid, refunded, and disputed payments for the current month and year only, instead of a flexible period defined by query parameters. These changes will improve the application's performance and data accuracy for audit logs and payment statistics.
